Allelic imbalances at copy neutral loss-of-heterozygosity in endometrial glands

Markdown file to present the methods to show allelic imbalances at copy neutral loss-of-heterozygosity in endometrial glands. Before you start the following analyses, please convert the corresponding excel source data files to tab-delimited text files. The source data files are provided in our paper (Yamaguchi et al. Nat Commun in press).

Clean up workspace

rm(list=ls())

Load libraries

library(ggplot2)

Visualize allelic imbalances at copy neutral loss-of-heterozygosity in endometrial glands

blue <- rgb(26/255, 115/255, 186/255, 1)
yellow <- rgb(255/255, 219/255, 67/255, 1)
orange <- rgb(181/255, 75/255, 5/255, 1)
red <- rgb(196/255, 0/255, 38/255, 1)

chr <- c(3, 10)
gland <- c("S36-C-13", "S36-C-15", "S36-D-2", "S36-D-4", "S36-D-18", "S36-D-20")

for (i in 1:length(chr)) {
  temp_data <- cnloh[cnloh$chr == chr[i], ]
  for (j in 1:length(gland)) {
    temp_data2 <- temp_data[temp_data$sample == gland[j], ]
    temp_title <- paste0("chr", chr[i])
    temp_title2 <- paste(gland[j], temp_title, sep = ": ")
    
    p_cnloh <- ggplot(temp_data2, aes(x=pos, y=norm_log_or, fill=norm_log_or))
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + geom_point(shape=22, size=2)
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + scale_fill_gradientn(
      colours=rev(c(red, "tomato", yellow, "lightblue", "darkblue")), 
      breaks=c(0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0), 
      values=c(0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1.0))
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + ggtitle(temp_title2)
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + xlab("Position on chromosome (MBp)")
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + ylab("Degree of allelic imbalance")
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + guides(fill=guide_colorbar(barwidth=3, barheight=7.5))
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + ylim(min(temp_data2$norm_log_or), max(temp_data2$norm_log_or))
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + xlim(0, max(temp_data2$pos))
    p_cnloh <- p_cnloh + theme(
      axis.text.x=element_text(size=20, color="black"), 
      axis.text.y=element_text(size=20, color="black"), 
      axis.title=element_text(size=20), 
      plot.title=element_text(size=20, color="black", hjust = 0.5),
      axis.line=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
      panel.grid.major=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
      panel.grid.minor=element_line(colour="#d3d3d3"),
      panel.border=element_rect(linetype="solid", fill=NA),
      panel.background=element_blank(),
      axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
      legend.position="none")
    
    print(p_cnloh)
  }
}
